FOR ACNE SUFFERERS -- Speeds Healing and Reduces Scarring!
Most important for acne sufferers is the ability to speed healing which reduces scarring. This is a priority for anyone suffering from acne. Excellent results are achieved by applying a thin layer of aloe vera gel on the affected skin. The enzymes in the gel relieve pain, reduce inflammation and decrease redness. As a result of accelerated healing, scarring is greatly reduced. Aloe vera has been proven to help those who suffer with Acne improve their condition and promote healing of scar tissue formed by excessive swelling and inflammation. The gel can be applied directly to any affected area.
It can be used either day or night, although some people prefer to apply it at night and wash it off in the morning. This method makes it act as a toner, to tighten the skin, making it look fresh and giving you a younger appearance when used on a regular basis.
Some little known applications of Aloe Vera: - Protects against underarm odor  - Eye wrinkle remover - An excellent shaving gel  - A hair styling gel  - Ends dandruff
What gives Aloe Vera its incredible Power to Heal, Protect, Nourish & Moisturize?
Aloe Vera contains allantoin (a valuable cell-proliferating healing agent that stimulates healthy tissue formation) which is what gives it its healing powers; increasing the availability of oxygen to the skin, and increasing the synthesis and strength of the skin itself.
Chemical analysis has shown the presence of mucopolysacharides, a natural moisturizing factor. It also moisturizes and rejuvenates the skin by stimulating synthesis of elastin and collagen speeding healing, reducing scarring, retarding aging, and penetrating with moisture carrying emollients that soak deep into the layers of the skin.
Aloe Vera contains the "youth mineral" potassium. It also contains naturally occurring antioxidants in the form of vitamins B complex, C and E, plus beta-carotene which is converted by the body into vitamin A; all needed desperately by the skin.
No matter what your skin type or condition, Aloe Vera provides the best possible protection.

Description:
Hand crafted to replicate the mysterious book Bastian finds that leads to an incredible journey. Begin your own journey with this leather bound book!

Generally you need the track to be twice the width of the door. If your door is 36" (3 feet) then you will need a 6 foot rail so the door can be completely close and open fully without overlapping the door opening.

Product name: tshirt dress, black dress, black cotton dress, summer dress, turquoise screenprint
Description:
Why do we call these Pineapple Flowers? They were inspired by a particular pineapple upside down cake my friend Lisa made about eight years ago. She had cut up all the fruit to try and spell the name of the birthday boy and, let's be honest, it looked a little crazy. We may have laughed at the cake's appearance, but cake is cake, and this cake was delicious.
Our whimsical illustrations bloom on a cotton dress in a rich black made exclusively for us by American Apparel. The fabric is breathable in the heat of summer, and it's long enough to leave the leggings behind. Summer only comes once a year, so tear through your front lawn and hop over your sprinkler! This dress wants an adventure.
Every shirt, dress, scarf, and skirt from Flytrap Clothing features our own original designs, and we screen print them by hand in our backyard workshop here in North Carolina. 
Fiber content:  100% cotton
Made in the USA
:: SIZING INFORMATION ::
Small / 30-32" bust
Medium / 32-34" bust
Large / 36-38" bust
X-Large / 39-40" bust
:: HOW TO DOUBLE CHECK YOUR SIZE ::
We get the sizing information above from our manufacturers and then double check it against feedback from our models and customers, but without having a fashion industry standard for what constitutes a "medium," we know that online shopping can be a bit of a guessing game. We want to get your order right the first time, so we came up with this time-tested, tried and true formula for the most accuracy in sizing: lay one of your favorite tees flat on a table, and measure the width across the chest, underneath the sleeves. Then you can compare that flat measurement with the following measurements and leave the guesswork behind!
Small / 15" flat measurement
Medium / 16" flat measurement
Large / 17" flat measurement
X-Large / 18" flat measurement
